:\n\n1. start from a branch, change, or PR\n2. use derived lookup indexes to find candidate turns and sessions\n3. resolve project-scoped sessions for those candidates\n4. read turns and observations for those sessions\n5. rank and explain the likely relationship from the underlying observations\n6. render the underlying transcript records for the selected windows\n\nFor a GitButler worktree with multiple applied branches, review sharing should\nbe able to show the whole associated session while highlighting the likely\nturns for the selected branch or PR. A narrower turn window can be selected\nlater without changing the session as the durable object.\n\nThe review product must not depend on a naive scan over all sessions and turns,\neven for the POC. The expected product query is:\n\n```text\ngiven a PR number or branch name, are there likely related agent sessions?\n```\n\nThat query needs an index-first read path. The system can still avoid persisted\n","tool_name":null,"tool_input":null,"source_record":{"timestamp":"2026-05-20T15:13:17.559Z","type":"response_item","payload":{"type":"function_call_output","call_id":"[REDACTED:entropy]"}}}